document_data.Powers:
When a spellcaster was hit by the Sword of Spells, they suffered as much as much damage as if they were hit by a regular longsword, but would fall unconscious immediately. Should they survive their wounds, they would find themselves slightly weakened but with knowledge of a brand new, rare and unfamiliar [[spell]].{{Cite dragon/417/Eye on the Realms: The Sword of Spells|26}}

When wounding warlocks, the sword would severe the pact binding them to their patron, causing them to lose their ability to wield arcane magic.{{Cite dragon/417/Eye on the Realms: The Sword of Spells|25,27}}

Here are some examples of spells bestowed by the sword to its victims:{{Cite dragon/417/Eye on the Realms: The Sword of Spells|26}}

* The ability to control the conflagration from [[fire]] spells such as ''[[fireball]]'' or ''[[wall of fire]]'', causing it to instantly jump to a different location within {{SI|120|feet|long=yes}}.
* The ability to create a floating [[illusion|illusory]] face similar from which the caster could see, speak, and cast spells.
* A teleportation spell similar to ''[[dimension door]]'', that could teleport the caster or simple objects over short distances thrice over 10 minutes.
* A spell damper that could cause part of the damage from incoming magic to be turned into harmless sounds and lights.

In addition the sword was particularly fast and nimble, allowing it to avoid mundane attempts of capture. It was also enchanted with a powerful [[spell reflection]] effect protecting it from magical attacks.
